      <p class="why__label">why this exists</p>
      <h2>You are about to make one of the biggest decisions of your life.</h2>
      <p>You know that moment when a lender says something like "your DTI is affecting your LTV and you may need PMI" and you just... nod? And smile? And write it down to Google later like a completely normal person? Yeah. That feeling is not your fault. The real estate industry loves its acronyms and assumes you speak fluent closing table. Most people don't.</p>
      <p>That is exactly why this exists. Once something clicks for me, I really get it. And once I get it, I cannot stop explaining it to people. Real estate clicked. Greenville clicked. Fifteen years of watching this city, more than a decade of analytical work, and one very strong opinion about natural light in listing photos later, here we are.</p>
      <blockquote>I was the person reading every line of every closing document like it was going to save my life. It kind of felt like it might. Now I make sure you never have to feel that way. You will know what everything means before it is ever in front of you.</blockquote>
      <cite>— Greenville Insider Editorial</cite>
      <p>I spent over ten years as an analyst across medical, legal, and business operations. Three very different fields, one consistent obsession: I was always the person who looked at the numbers everyone else was summarizing and thought "wait, that's not actually what this says."</p>
      <p>My husband is a Greenville native which means I had a very good tour guide when I arrived fifteen years ago. I stayed because obviously. Since then I have watched this city transform from the inside, and developed opinions about all the neighborhoods and I am not shy about sharing.</p>
      <p>Honestly? I just love helping people. The Greenville Insider is how I do that before you ever need me. So that when the moment comes, you already feel ready.</p>
      <div class="why__newsletter">
        <h3>Join the Greenville Insider</h3>
        <p>Weekly notes on the Greenville market, new listings, and the kind of guidance nobody gives you until you're already confused at the closing table. Consider this your head start.</p>
        <a href="https://hannah-labadorf-realtor.kit.com/e551679830" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn--primary">Send me the homework.</a>
        <p class="why__fine">Free. Once a week. The worst thing that happens is you learn something about the Greenville market.</p>
      </div>
